This was the most amazing white chocolate mousse I've ever tried! I made this for my book club dinner, to follow a pretty heavy Italian alfredo pasta meal, so it was perfect and light enough to finish the evening with. I took a few shortcuts to save time and/or money: an inexpensive brut champagne left at my house after some party, regular E&J brandy instead of pear brandy, and cream cheese mixed with 1/2 c whipping cream to achieve a mascarpone consistency. I also added sliced toasted almonds in the layering process, to give it more crunch. I couldn't find pear nectar or ladyfingers, so I pureed sliced pears in syrup for the pear nectar (to make 2 cups' worth), and I had to make ladyfingers from scratch. Time- consuming, but worth it, and you can avoid the HFCS found in most prepared cookies. Will definitely make this again!

