Rating: 2
SO so so sweet. Made this for Christmas and everyone else said they liked it but I didn't. I even reduced the sugar in the poaching syrup to 2/3 cup and it still knocked me over in one bite. However, it does have potential, so this is what I would recommend (unless you like to mainline your sugar): Use only about 1/3 c. sugar in the poaching syrup, and increase the spices. Reduce the white chocolate to about 5 oz. and add two egg yolks to the mouse, during the cooking phase--put them in like you're making hollandaise sauce. Definitely watch the temp. on the mousse, keep it just a little warm for mixing. White cake or angel food cake would work better than lady fingers, which get a bit grainy when soaked with syrup. I also would use only about 2 1/2 cups poaching syrup because it goes a long way. This dessert is BEAUTIFUL to look at however, so with some tweaking, it could be a great "blonde" dessert go-to.

