Rating: 3
i tried to make this dessert for Thanksgiving. My mousse curdled twice, and i had to substitute with my own white chocolate mousse recipe. If you want to make this dessert, i recommend that you let mascarpone cool down to room temperature. This was not specified in the recipe, and i suspect that the temperature difference between the components of the mousse was the culprit in my case. Also, cheese and mousse emulsions curdle when overbeaten, so make sure you fold rather than beat or whip.

